The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, August 24, 2003 				 Husband kills wife
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Aug. 23: Soumi Chakroborty, 22, was shot dead allegedly by her husband at his grandfathers empty flat on Hari Pada Dutta Lane in south Calcutta tonight.																								Soumi, a student of Class XI, was married to Tuhin Chakroborty for three years, though a divorce case was on, police said.																								Soumis parents informed Tuhins father, Tapan Chakroborty, as their daughter was getting late to return home.																								Tapan then went to the flat where he found that the lights were on but the door was locked from inside. He broke open the flat to find the two lying in a pool of blood.																								Soumi had been shot close to the ear, while her husband had shot himself on the hand, police said. Tuhin has been admitted to the MR Bangur Hospital and has been arrested.																								Police have recovered three firearms from the flat, deputy superintendent of police (town), Humayun Kabir said. Tapan has been held for interrogation.
